1
00:00:00,404 --> 00:00:02,577
My name
is Oliver Queen.

2
00:00:02,578 --> 00:00:04,356
After five years in hell,

3
00:00:04,358 --> 00:00:06,372
I have come home
with only one goal--

4
00:00:06,373 --> 00:00:08,246
to save my city.

5
00:00:08,248 --> 00:00:10,385
Now others have
joined my crusade.

6
00:00:10,387 --> 00:00:12,761
To them, I'm Oliver Queen.

7
00:00:12,763 --> 00:00:16,169
To the rest of Starling City,
I am someone else.

8
00:00:16,171 --> 00:00:19,305
I am...something else.

9
00:00:19,307 --> 00:00:20,742
Previously, on "Arrow"...

10
00:00:20,744 --> 00:00:22,481
I killed Sara.

11
00:00:22,483 --> 00:00:24,848
Malcolm gave me something
that made me

12
00:00:24,850 --> 00:00:26,951
susceptible to suggestion.

13
00:00:26,953 --> 00:00:28,614
What happened wasn't
your fault, Thea,

14
00:00:28,616 --> 00:00:30,381
because it wasn't
your decision.

15
00:00:30,383 --> 00:00:32,747
Malcolm? He's going
to face justice.

16
00:00:32,749 --> 00:00:36,791
He's gone. Malcolm Merlyn
will never be seen again.

17
00:00:38,991 --> 00:00:41,259
Welcome to Nanda Parbat.

18
00:00:41,261 --> 00:00:43,561
When I told you
that Malcolm killed Sara,

19
00:00:43,563 --> 00:00:45,789
he wanted her dead,
but I am the one

20
00:00:45,791 --> 00:00:48,027
who fired those arrows
into her chest.

21
00:00:48,029 --> 00:00:50,330
I promised you your vengeance.

22
00:00:52,701 --> 00:00:55,496
So take it.

23
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:59,827
Kill me.

24
00:00:59,829 --> 00:01:03,032
But spare
John Diggle's life.

25
00:01:03,034 --> 00:01:05,827
Let him go.

26
00:01:07,930 --> 00:01:10,221
I will beg for it.

27
00:01:10,223 --> 00:01:12,426
You've shown
tremendous strength,

28
00:01:12,428 --> 00:01:14,086
fortitude,

29
00:01:14,088 --> 00:01:16,187
and power.

30
00:01:17,259 --> 00:01:19,422
No, Mr. Queen...

31
00:01:19,424 --> 00:01:23,417
I don't want to kill you.

32
00:01:23,419 --> 00:01:25,783
I want you to take my place.

33
00:01:26,953 --> 00:01:30,884
I want you to become
the next Ra's al Ghul.

34
00:01:30,886 --> 00:01:34,426
Ra's is a title greater
than any one man.

35
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:37,726
Wing ta Lao wo chey.

36
00:01:41,861 --> 00:01:44,920
Am I supposed to understand
what that means?

37
00:01:44,922 --> 00:01:49,460
No. It is from a dialect
no longer spoken.

38
00:01:49,462 --> 00:01:52,323
Said to me by a man
whose place I took.

39
00:01:52,325 --> 00:01:55,656
Contemplating the same offer.

40
00:01:55,658 --> 00:01:57,989
And what it means is,

41
00:01:57,991 --> 00:02:00,659
a tale to be told...

42
00:02:00,661 --> 00:02:02,727
begins thus.

43
00:02:11,527 --> 00:02:12,987
Ayy!

44
00:02:35,734 --> 00:02:38,698
Don't let your footing
betray you.

45
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,896
Let your power come not from
the strength of your attack

46
00:02:40,898 --> 00:02:43,230
but from the ground
that holds your feet.

47
00:02:48,172 --> 00:02:52,302
All men seek guidance,
a purpose.

48
00:02:52,304 --> 00:02:55,572
The means to live
without pain.

49
00:02:55,574 --> 00:02:58,664
Those who journey here have given
such an exchange

50
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:01,397
for their fealty.

51
00:03:02,121 --> 00:03:04,636
You mean they have
to kill for you?

52
00:03:06,839 --> 00:03:10,412
No, Mr. Queen,
they have to die for me.

53
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:24,622
Is all of this supposed
to impress me?

54
00:03:24,624 --> 00:03:26,662
No.

55
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,997
It's to inform you.

56
00:03:28,999 --> 00:03:32,364
Surely men have
branded you a murderer,

57
00:03:32,366 --> 00:03:34,163
a torturer.

58
00:03:34,165 --> 00:03:39,433
But see, I would never
shame you with such bluntness.

59
00:03:39,435 --> 00:03:43,606
Because I see it
in your eyes.

60
00:03:43,608 --> 00:03:47,173
The struggle you have
with your dual identity.

61
00:03:47,175 --> 00:03:49,846
Oliver Queen and the Arrow.

62
00:03:49,848 --> 00:03:52,279
Neither are giving you
what you crave.

63
00:03:52,281 --> 00:03:54,983
But becoming
Ra's al Ghul will?

64
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:59,120
Oliver Queen is a man
destined to be alone.

65
00:03:59,122 --> 00:04:02,590
He loves a woman
he knows he cannot have.

66
00:04:02,592 --> 00:04:04,155
You don't know me.

67
00:04:04,157 --> 00:04:05,689
But I know the Arrow.

68
00:04:05,691 --> 00:04:08,351
"Al Sahhim."
You will never be

69
00:04:08,353 --> 00:04:11,323
anything more than a vigilante
for those whose lives you save

70
00:04:11,325 --> 00:04:13,353
at the risk of your own.

71
00:04:13,355 --> 00:04:17,158
And the city will turn on you,

72
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,554
and your closest allies
within the police department

73
00:04:19,556 --> 00:04:21,816
will call you a criminal.

74
00:04:21,818 --> 00:04:24,055
You will be scorned

75
00:04:24,057 --> 00:04:26,053
and hunted,

76
00:04:26,055 --> 00:04:27,692
and then killed.

77
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:31,953
Dying as you began
your crusade...

78
00:04:33,394 --> 00:04:35,852
Alone.

79
00:04:35,876 --> 00:04:39,876
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Arrow 3x16 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Offer</font>
